## Public Member Attributes

### GV {#a5a4bce26dd4a1eb0f4c7a629dc600508}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>const GlobalValue&#42; llvm::GlobalValueSummaryInfo::NameOrGV::GV</>}>
The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/globalvalue">GlobalValue</a> corresponding to this summary.

This is only used in per-module summaries and when the IR is available. E.g. when module analysis is being run, or when parsing both the IR and the summary from assembly.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/modulesummaryindex-h/#l00151">151</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/modulesummaryindex-h">ModuleSummaryIndex.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### Name {#a631e4319a528f18fac78c07744da2d69}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="StringRef llvm::GlobalValueSummaryInfo::NameOrGV::Name">
Summary string representation.

This <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> points to BC module string table and is valid until module data is stored in memory. This is guaranteed to happen until runThinLTOBackend function is called, so it is safe to use this field during thin link. This field is only valid if summary index was loaded from BC file.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/modulesummaryindex-h/#l00158">158</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/modulesummaryindex-h">ModuleSummaryIndex.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
